gy and philosophy of religion of adopting such an approach.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aReligion and science. 0aTheologyxMethodology. 4aHistory Of Science. 4aHistory. 4aReligious Studies. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172453440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501724534423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501724534/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles